item.media:title: [+Video] OC - Vox Revamp!
item.media:description:
Yes it's Vox, but better
 

Time-lapse video available, click here to watch!   

I've been thinking for a while that I wanted to revamp Vox, and at same time create a Noxdroid for the species + official group mascot!

She is originally named Vox because she could sing/was music related. But now she lost that ability due the virus and only the name remained. She still has a pretty voice though.
I got super excited to have her as new OC... since all active ones are happy-go-luck type xD it's refreshing to have a villain in the list!

On side note, she will still upgrade and change, so this is just the beginning 8D
That's how she was before (art from 2014):

item.title: Here's your bag back
item.media:title: Here's your bag back
item.media:description:
What did you expect?" Sato asked him, his red eyes glaring down on him, a faint glow still in his irises.
Masaru didn't know what to expect. He never expected anything, maybe that was his problem. He stopped expecting things ever since his family died and he ended up alone. In his mind he already resigned to his own death by then.
"I... don't know" he uttered.
"Exraion is no place for an auraless person." Sato's eyes glided over the damage he'd done, completely expressionless. He didn't feel. A monster without emotions, he even admitted to that himself. Yet that little monster had protected Masaru from the scum in the outer city more than once.
"Here's you bag back" Sato stated as he dropped the thing on the ground. "Make sure it doesn't get stolen again."
Masaru nodded, silently. He felt a little nauseous, the taste of blood still in his mouth. And it didn't get better thinking about the damage that was done. He couldn't stand blood. He never could, regardless of how bad those people were. A weakness they'd already mocked him for more than once.
"Oh, and do me a favor" Sato continued, as if he hadn't noticed. "Get out of here. Find yourself a fancy apartment somewhere in the inner city. You're no good out here."

item.title: DnD - Linnaea
item.media:title: DnD - Linnaea
item.media:description:
So I started watching/listening to Critical Role last year....

This year i decided to change things a bit, and I got bold, and joined a party of strangers for a game of DnD.
Possibly the best random thing i've ever done lol.

My character is a half-elven "cleric". I can't tell much about her yet, so that I won't spoil it for the others. And yes, i'm planning to paint every party member, eventually
I know, my art style and design choices are totally different to the classic DnD arts, but I guess I wanted to make my own version of it a little bit~

She is possibly the closest character to my own personality so far that i've ever created, and also an attempt to overcome some personal things and force some changes in my life that will push me into a more healthy lifestyle.
Namely the fact that most artists are complete loners.
I haven't really met people in the past decade
After only one meeting I have more energy and motivation to care more about myself and of course, I can't wait to be in their company again.
It is very surreal to think about how rare it is that we can meet likeminded people. It takes a lot of effort to take steps, and it is always a risk , especially after some bad experiences, but
Don't be afraid. Go out there, give another chance.
Worst thing that can happen is that time passes  by and you realize that actually nothing ever happens to you.

And I know, I don't share much about myself online, even my name means "concealed". But i'll try to post more "stories" about the art I do, and I'll try to interact with people a bit more.
Do you have any specific wishes you'd like to know? Certain tutorial types, art tips, stories about the art journey? Anything specific?

And of course, thank you so much for the support over the years, and for just stopping by!
If you have any DnD stories to tell, i'm happy to read your experiences! <3

item.title: Stegosaurus
item.media:title: Stegosaurus
item.media:description:
Prints: daniel-eskridge.pixels.com/fea…

A grey and brown stegosaurus, a herbivorous dinosaur, stands on a pile of boulders looking down on a late Jurassic era forest of conifers. 3D Rendering

This is my first image to feature a stegosaurus.

How I make art like this: fineartbydaniel.com/2017/12/18…

Thanks for looking!
Daniel Eskridge

P.S. Before you comment, please read my  standard paleoart disclaimer:
When it comes to paleoart, the images I create favor 'art' more than 'paleo'. While I try my best to depict animals as accurately as possible, I'm make no claim that they 100% scientifically accurate. The same goes for the environment I depict them in. I am primarily interested in creating aesthetically pleasing images and paintings. Scientific accuracy comes second behind artistic expression.

Credits:
Base Stegosaurus Model by DinoRaul (introvertartist.com/stegosauru…)
Posing done using Poser (IntrovertArtist.com/Poser)
Retexturing/Resculpting done in ZBrush (IntrovertArtist.com/ZBrush)
Environment and Rendering done in Vue (IntrovertArtist.com/Vue)
Compositing and Painting done in Photoshop CS (fineartbydaniel.com/2018/02/03…)
Color enhancement done using Photomatix (IntrovertArtist.com/Photomatix)
